&gt; &gt; Sure I can.  How can I get a 200 OK for a nonexistent resource?
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; ---&gt; http://www.infoq.com/author/Darth-Vader
&gt; 

That&#39;s a URI.  Therefore it must identify a resource.  If dereferencing
that resource responds 200 OK, then the resource must, by definition,
exist.  Reading the response entity tells me that the resource is
defined to be a list of &quot;All of Darth Vader&#39;s Content on InfoQ&quot; and
contains no links.  So the resource is exactly what its hypertext
representation says it is.  If I want to know whether &quot;Darth Vader is
alive&quot; then why would I query this resource?  It isn&#39;t defined to be
about that, is it?

-Eric
